notes.text: An update for libtirpc is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
The libtirpc packages contain SunLib's implementation of transport-independent remote procedure call (TI-RPC) documentation, which includes a library required by programs in the nfs-utils and rpcbind packages.

For detailed information on changes in this release, see the Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.4 Release Notes linked from the References section.

Users of libtirpc are advised to upgrade to these updated packages.

notes.text: A null-pointer dereference vulnerability was found in libtirpc.  The return value of makefd_xprt() was not checked in all instances, which could lead to a crash when the server exhausted the maximum number of available file descriptors.  A remote attacker could cause an rpc-based application to crash by flooding it with new connections.
